<h4>4 directions</h4>
<p> By changing the value of data-placement to define <code>top</code>, <code>right</code>, <code>bottom</code> or <code>left</code>.
<div class="bs-docs-example">
<a title="" data-placement="top" rel="tooltip" data-toggle="tooltip" href="#" data-original-title="Tooltip on Top">Tooltip on top ---</a>
<a title="" data-placement="right" rel="tooltip" data-toggle="tooltip" href="#" data-original-title="Tooltip on Right">Tooltip on right ---</a>
<a title="" data-placement="bottom" rel="tooltip" data-toggle="tooltip" href="#" data-original-title="Tooltip on Bottom">Tooltip on bottom ---</a>
<a title="" data-placement="left" rel="tooltip" data-toggle="tooltip" href="#" data-original-title="Tooltip on Left">Tooltip on left</a>
</div>
        </section>
  <section id="S2">
           <div class="page-header">
            <h1> Popover</h1>
          </div>
          <p>Popover is used to provide short description about specific items such as help, item detail information...</p>
          <div class="bs-docs-example">
           <div class="parentPosition" style="display:inline-block;">
<i class="uiIconQuestion uiIconLightGray"></i>
<div class="gotPosition" style="position: absolute;">
<div class="popover right bbcodePopupContent" style="width: 230px; top: -63.4px; left: 10px; display: none;">
<span class="arrow" style="top: 30%;"></span>
<div class="popover-content">This is a sample piece of BBCode to use as an example for this particular BBCode. For example, to demonstrate the use of the [b] tag, enter [b]Some Text[/b].</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>
 	<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;div class=" "&gt; &lt;i class="uiIconQuestion uiIconLightGray"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
         
	</section>
<h4>4 directions</h4>
<p>Four options are available: top, right, bottom, and left aligned.</p>
<div class="bs-docs-example">
<a>Popover on Top ---</a>
<a>Popover on Right ---</a>
<a>Popover on Bottom ---</a>
<a>Popover on Left</a>
</div>
	</section>
